RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 1 7F Dirt CR: 65. Claiming Purse 13000. FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ONE MORE SLEEP was off mid pack, moved into a stalking position while racing in the three path, raced in between foes, moved after the half and shifted out into the four path, launched a bid at the three eighths pole, raced four wide while circling, challenged for the lead at the five sixteenth pole, took command at the quarter pole, led through the stretch run with the same rival he passed at the quarter pole, was under pressure the whole stretch but was bale to hole sway for the win. CALLEN FEELS GOOD vied for the lead, settled back just off of the leader and stalked in the four path, advanced and took control at the three eighths pole, was challenged by another rival at the five sixteenth pole, battled until the quarter pole where he relinquished the lead, chased that rival all the way down the stretch but could not get the lead back finishing second. PERFECT STRIKE was off mid pack, raced on the rail, settled in hands and saved ground through out, was asked and to close and responded well holding off a late running rival for third. TOOCAN DANCE was off bit slow, raced in the three path, was encouraged in the turn, found his best stride late making up ground in the stretch, just missed for third. OCEAN KISS vied for the lead, settled off of the pace and stalked, moved at the half mile pole, maintained position through the turn, was encouraged in the stretch but had no rally. BROOK IS GOLDEN vied for the lead, led while racing on the rail, set the pace under pressure, started to faded at the five sixteenth pole, then struggled to switch leads in the stretch. K V TARGET was off slow, ran from off of the pace, settled, bid at the three eighths pole, but could not get involved. LOWER CRETACEOUS vied for the lead, stalked the pace, raced three wide and in between horses then faded. PER LOUISIANA RULING 25225, ONE MORE SLEEP WAS DISQUALIFIED FROM FIRST TO UNPLACED FOR A MEDICATION VIOLATION.

MODOC raced from off of the pace in the two path, launched a bid at the three eights pole, split rivals in the turn, closed well in the stretch hitting his best stride. HOWL YEAH raced from off of the pace in the eight path, shifted into the four path through the turn made a mild bid late. WINDTAPPER WIN raced off of the pace in the six path, briefly improved position then faded.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Alabama Cotton State S. LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 6 6F Dirt CR: 90. Stakes Purse 50000. FOR REGISTERED ALABAMA BRED THREE YEAR OLD AND UPWARD. No nomination. No entry or start fee. $50,000 Guaranteed of which 60% to the winner, 20% to second, 11% to third, 6% to fourth, and 3% to fifth. Weights: Three Year Old 122 lbs.; Older 124 lbs. Non wi nners of a race since since June 19, 2023 allowed 2 lbs. Non winners of a race since February 19, 2023 allowed 4 lbs. Maidens are allowed 6 lbs. In the event that more than twelve (12) horses pass the entry box, preference will be given to the horses with the highest earnings in 2022 - 2023. Different owners will have equal draw according to earnings. The second part of same owner entries will have no consideration over a single interest. Alabama Breeders Association will present a trophy to the winning o wner. Nominations Closed Monday August 7, 2023 with 9 Nominees.
